text: Very European looking building called Tudor Court Shopping Mall, lined with nice Europe architecture with shoppings along the ground level.
It's okay. A few arty shops and stuff but building looking a bit tired.
This is where we were living when I was born!!  The  address is seen on my birth cert!   It was government staff quarters those days, and my dad was a civil servant.
A few shops only but the building looks classic German/ Alsace style. Unusual for Singapore.
A row of colonial style shophouses housing a variety of small businesses. This place is expensive as it is located in Tanglin.
